Description. Female . Body length about 1.0 mm. Body dark brown with green or blue sheen; antenna (
Fig. 32
) generally yellow, but pedicle dorsally and clava apically dark brownish; fore wing (
Fig. 33
) hyaline, but about apical 1 / 3 slightly infuscate; legs (
Figs 34−36
) yellowish, hind femur generally dark brown, mid and hind coxae often yellow, rarely brownish-yellow, mid tibia basally rarely marked with dark brown.

Thorax. Fore wing about 2.5 × as long as broad; marginal vein long, nearly 3 × as long as broad; postmarginal vein about 1 / 3 as long as marginal vein; stigmal vein about half as long as marginal vein (
Fig. 33
).

Distribution. Barbados , China (new record), Fiji , Ghana , Grenada , India , Indonesia , Japan , Madagascar , Mauritius , Pakistan , St Christopher (Kitts) & Nevis , St. Vincent , Tanzania , Trinidad & Tobago , Turkmenistan , USA (
Hayat 1986
;
Trjapitzin 1989
;
Noyes 2002
;
Trjapitzin et al. 2004
).
